People's Org.s Vow to Greet Important =Anniv. Next Year with Shining Successes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The working people's organizations in the DPRK held plenary meetings to vow to greet the 95th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung and the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il and the 75th founding anniversary of the Korean People's Army with high political zeal and shining labor achievements.
 The 56th plenary meeting of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, the 48th plenary meeting of the Central Committee of the Korean Democratic Women's Union and the 52nd plenary meeting of the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea separately took place here on Sept. 19, 20 and 21. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the plenary meetings proposed tasks to be undertaken to energetically conduct the organizational and political work for significantly marking important anniversaries next year with a view to firmly preserving the revolutionary feats performed by the President and glorifying them generation after generation and making a tangible contribution to the accomplishment of the Songun revolutionary cause of the Workers' Party of Korea and ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The plenary meetings called on the working people's organizations at all levels and their officials to dynamically conduct an ideological educational work to eternally hold the President in high esteem as the father of socialist Korea and the sun of Juche, defend the headquarters of revolution politically and ideologically and with their lives and more firmly uphold the Songun idea and leadership of the Party.
 The plenary meetings underlined the need for the working people's organizations to pay primary attention to thoroughly ensuring the political and ideological purity of their ranks and augmenting the military power of the country in every way and conduct a variety of vigorous mass movements to bring about a boost in the production in all sectors and at all units of economic construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meetings also called for earnestly introducing the revolutionary soldier culture created in the era of Songun to make a fresh leap forward in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation, holding higher the red flag of revolution and loudly singing songs of revolution and struggle.

DPRK Birthday Observed Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held by the Saratov Association for the Study of the Juche Idea and Songun Policy of Russia, the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Songun Policy, the Kim Il Sung Institute of Agricultural Science in Guinea and the Tunisia-Korea Friendship Association from Sept. 7 to 9 on the occasion of the birthday of the DPRK. A photo exhibition and film show were held by the Indian Institute for Foreign Policy Studies and film shows were arranged by a firm and company of Malaysia, a stock company of Zimbabwe and the Czech Taekwon-Do Association from Sept. 5 to 8 on the same occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venue of the photo exhibition were photos introducing the proud path covered by the DPRK and participants of film shows watched Korean films.
 Speakers at functions referred to the exploits President Kim Il Sung performed in the nation-building, recalling that the DPRK has demonstrated its might as a socialist powerful country independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence under his wise leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that Korean-style socialism is sure to triumph under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, they stated the Korean people will build a great prosperous powerful nation and surely achieve the country's reunification in the near future under his wise leadership.
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held by the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Songun Policy.

National School Youth and Children's Games Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The swimming contests of the 32nd National Games of School Youth and Children for "Jong Il Peak Cup," the swimming contests of the University Student Games for "September 5 Cup" and the 10th National Basketball Games of Youth and Students for "August 28 Youth Cup" took place here from Sept. 13 to 20.
 In the swimming contests of the games for "Jong Il Peak Cup" the boy swimmers of the Pyongyang Wisong Middle School and the girl swimmers of the Pyongyang Tonghung Middle School emerged the winners in the middle school group and the boy swimmers of the elementary course of the Chilbong Middle School in Chongdan County and the girl swimmers of the Pyongyang Kum Song Street Primary School emerged supreme in the primary school group in total points. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the swimming contests for "September 5 Cup" boys and girls of   Kim Il Sung University captured the title in the university group and boys of Pyongyang Sungho College of Building Materials and girls of Pyongyang College of Electrical Engineering finished the winners in the college group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 First prize went to the men and women cagers of Kim Il Sung University in the university group at the basketball games of youth and students for "August 28 Youth Cup." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The men players of South Hamgyong Province finished on the top in the working youth group.

Architectural Aesthetic Symposium Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- A symposium on architectural aesthetics of Pyongyang Kim Won Gyun Conservatory was held at the Concert Hall of the conservatory on Sept. 21.
 Presented to the symposium were five papers proving the architectural aesthetic characteristic of the conservatory which has been built as a monument of the times under the loving care for posterity and wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.
 The speakers explained in detail that the unique theme of depiction defining the seed, content and form in building the conservatory was made clear by his energetic guidance, so that Juche character, modernity, plastic character and artistic quality could be combined in all components of architectural formation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Organic combination of architecture and fine arts is an important guarantee for increasing the plastic character and artistic quality of the buildings, they said, stressing that the main building of the conservatory, the mark of the concert hall, main painting "Blue Sky over My Country" on the front wall of the lobby of the hall, a bust of Composer Kim Won Gyun and other sculptures and harmoniously graven pattern decorations are conducive to clarifying the character and mission of the conservatory in a plastic and artistic way and dignifying the buildings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They discussed the tasks and ways to erect many more buildings to suit people's aesthetic desire and demand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the symposium were Pae Tal Jun, minister of State Construction Control who is chairman of the Central Committee of the Korean Union of Architects, officials concerned, architectural designers and technicians and officials of architectural scientific and educational institutions.

Reception Given on Army Day of Egypt 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Ahmed Medhat, military attache of the Egyptian embassy here, hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on Sept. 21 on the occasion of the army day of Egypt.
 Present on invitation were generals and officers of the Korean People's Army, officials concerned, diplomatic envoys of different countries, representatives of international organizations and military attaches of foreign embassies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Egyptian Ambassador Moustafa Mohamed Ahmed Al Hatter and embassy officials were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Speeches were made there.

Kim Jong Suk, Great Woman Soldier 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Suk is still alive in the minds of the Korean people as woman commander of Mt. Paektu, anti-Japanese war hero and distinguished bodyguard.
 Keenly experienced the tragedy of national ruin by the Japanese imperialists in her early years, she joined in Sept. Juche 24 (1935) the Korean People's Revolutionary Army (KPRA) organized and led by President Kim Il Sung, kicking off her revolutionary life as a great woman soldier. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She regarded it as the first mission of the arms to defend Commander Kim Il Sung, who was shouldering the destiny of the Korean nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She, a matchless crack-shot, distinguished herself by guarding the revolutionary headquarters at a lot of battles including the battle on the outskirts of Dashahe, the battle at Fusong county town and the battle at Hongqihe, thus setting a model of bodyguard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In hundreds of battles during the anti-Japanese war, she fully demonstrated her keen perspicacity, accurate judgment, unrivalled courage and superb tactics as a woman commander of the guerrilla army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Even after the liberation of the country she, as a bodyguard of the headquarters, did her best to protect the personal safety of the President and poured her heart and soul into building a regular armed forces of revolution.
 She frequented Pyongyang Institute, the Security Officers Training Center and other schools and training centers at all levels, leading the trainees to be servicemen of the leader armed with the revolutionary ideas and Juche-based tactics of the President and anti-Japanese guerilla method and style of work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was Kim Jong Suk who implanted in the mind of leader Kim Jong Il the idea that the Korean revolution should be accomplished at the point of bayonet.
 He, remaining true to the noble intention of his mother, has firmly defended and successfully carried forward the Juche-based revolutionary cause with arms in the grave revolutionary struggle for many years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The precious life of Kim Jong Suk serves as a source of patriotic zeal of the Korean people, who are striving hard to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation while giving priority to the army.

DPRK Law on Co-operative Production of Castings Adopted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea adopted the Law on Co-operative Production of Castings in August 2006.
 The mission of the law is to fully meet the demand of the national economy for casting goods by establishing a strict system and order in the production of castings.
 The law consists of 27 articles in all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Stipulated in the law are the issues of principle to be abided by in the co-operative production of castings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It gives a solid legal guarantee to constantly increase casting production in accordance with the requirement of the developing reality by realizing the standardization of castings and the specialization and concentration of their production.

Wreaths Laid before Bust of Kim Jong Suk 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the bust of Kim Jong Suk, anti-Japanese war hero, at the Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong Friday on the occasion of the 57th anniversary of her demise. 
 Standing there was a wreath sent by leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were senior officials of the party, the army and the state, the chairman of a friendly party, leading officials of working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army and working people and school youth and children in the city. 
 Placed there were wreaths in the name of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and the DPRK Cabinet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also laid there were wreaths in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, working people's organizations, ministries, national institutions, units of the Korean People's Army, scientific, educational, public health and media organizations, the Joint National Organization of the Korean Children's Union, party and power bodies, factories and farms in Pyongyang and bouquets. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid silent tribute to Kim Jong Suk, recollecting her noble revolutionary life and exploits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, floral baskets were also placed before her statues standing in Kim Jong Suk County in Ryanggang Province, Hoeryong City in North Hamgyong Province and at Kim Jong Suk Naval Academy and Kim Jong Suk General Military School.
 A floral basket was laid before her statue in Hoeryong City by a delegation of a co. ltd., in Helong City of China.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from Participants in Film Festival
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il received a letter from the participants in the 10th Pyongyang International Film Festival on Friday. 
 The festival was all the more significant one as it was well organized and flawless, the letter said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the festival we have come to understand well that  Kim Jong Il has paid special concern to the movie sector long ago and energetically guided movie-making to open a heyday in the development of Korean movies. We were moved to see good feature films "A Schoolgirl's Diary" and "Pyongyang Nalpharam" reflecting the fresh development of Korean movies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seeing with our own eyes all the Korean moviemen ardently revering Your Excellency Kim Jong Il as their benevolent father and dear teacher, we have been convinced that Korean movie art will make leaping progress in the future as long as they are under your wise leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Short as our stay in your country was, we could realize that the secret that the Korean people wrought world-startling miracles one after another, bravely breaking through difficulties lies in the single-minded unity of the leader and the people. 
 Availing ourselves of this opportunity, we extend heartfelt thanks to Your Excellency Kim Jong Il for always paying so deep concern that the festival may successfully be held true to the expectation of progressive people and moviemen of the world.
 Independence, peace and friendship are the lofty idea of the Pyongyang Festival and the common desire of the progressive people of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
.$B!!.(BWe will in the future, too, sincerely participate in the festival and make positive efforts for the development of genuine movie art suitable to the desire of the progressives.

"Transfer of Right to Command Wartime Operations" Termed Move for New War
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Korean National Peace Committee in a statement Friday termed the "transfer of the right to command wartime operations" much touted by the U.S. and the south Korean military authorities moves to round off the preparations for the second Korean war and ignite it any moment according to the U.S. new anti-north war strategy.
 Recalling that the commander of the U.S. forces in south Korea blustered they would stage joint military exercises in keeping with the "transfer of the right to command wartime operations" separately from "Ulji Focus Lens" and "RSOI," the statement noted that the U.S. is contemplating using the south Korean army as a shock brigade for a war against the north and bullet shields for the U.S. troops under the signboard of transferring the above-said right. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is meaningless to talk about the "transfer of the right to command wartime operations" as long as the U.S. military presence and domination over south Korea go on. It is, therefore, no more than a third-rate drama. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. only seeks to perpetuate the military presence in south Korea and launch a war of aggression against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the south Korean military authorities are hell bent on the moves for a war against the north under the signboard of the "self-reliant defence." This is an extremely hideous crime against the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that there can be neither self-reliance nor improved inter-Korean relations as long as the south Korean military authorities beg for the U.S. forces' permanent presence in south Korea and zealously join foreign forces in the war moves to stifle fellow countrymen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people should resolutely reject the war moves stepped up by the U.S. and south Korean military warlike forces behind the curtain of the "transfer of the right to command wartime operations" and vigorously turn out in the struggle to get the U.S. imperialist aggressor troops withdrawn from south Korea at an early date.
